p: \bCongratulations, \pn.
\bYou've beaten all of us. The strongest trainers in history.
\bAnd because of that... we feel you'd be the best person to protect this region with us.
\bI want to grant you the title of Augur.
\bThe Third Augur, the new protector of the region.
\bCongratulations!
\bObviously this gives you responsibility... but nothing you aren't already doing!
\bBut now... there's so many people to help.
\bFor example, the people at the Scientists Club would love your assistance.
\bPerhaps somebody in Deyraan Town or the Nightmare Realm would have something for you.
\bAnd you'll definitely get calls from time to time from friends asking for your aid!
\bAnd, I'd like to entrust you with these.
Kernel.pbReceiveItem(PBItems::CRYSTALPIECE,3)
\bI think they'll be safest in your hands.
\bBut, I want to reiterate again, the region is an open door to you now. Explore!
\bExploring will be rewarded- a keen eye could be rewarded with a Battle Frontier, quests, and a whole new region to explore!
\bGood luck, \pn. Thank you.

\b\pn, it's good to see you again.
\bCongratulations on your recent victory! Over both the Elite Four, and over Nyx.
\bThis is where we stay. The Timeless. The eight trainers plucked from history chosen to guard that crystal you found.
\bBut, now that Nyx was defeated...
\bThe biggest threat to those crystal shards is gone.
\bI suppose we will disband soon enough. We'll give you back the pieces you've won- there's no reason to guard them any more.
\bBut there's one last task we have before we can split.
\bYou see, when we gave Adam that crystal, it made him the guardian of the region.
\bWe chose the First Augur. While we weren't able to choose the second, it's only appropriate we choose the next one.
\bLooking around, there's only one trainer in Torren who I know is capable of protecting it as well as Adam could.
\bThe one who saved our entire universe- you, \pn.
\bBut, there are formalities to observe.
\bIf you want to guard the region, you're going to have to show us what you're made of.
\bDon't worry. We're not sadists! You're perfectly welcome to heal your Pokemon in between bouts.
\bThis isn't some kind of Elite Seven.
\bWhen you defeat the main seven of us, the way to our leader will open.
\bPlease, take your time. We're in no rush- but we do need to choose a new Augur!
A
